==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Swinge
<hw>Swinge</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Swinged</conjf> <pr>(sw⟦icr⟧njd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Swingeing</conjf> <pr>(sw⟦icr⟧nj"⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>.]</vmorph>
<ety>[OE. <ets>swengen</ets>, AS. <ets>swengan</ets> to shake, causative
of <ets>swingan</ets>. See <er>Swing</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
beat soundly; to whip; to chastise; to punish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I had <qex>swinged</qex> him soundly.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And <qex>swinges</qex> his own vices in his son.</q> <rj><qau>C.
Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To move as a lash; to lash.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Swinges</qex> the scaly horror of his folded tail.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swinge</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Swinge
<hw>Swinge</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The sweep of anything in
motion; a swinging blow; a swing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Waller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Power; sway; influence.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swingebuckler</ent>⟦br⟧
